                    %a{:href => "#"} Separated link 2
          / /.nav-collapse
    .container
      .hero-unit
        %h1#fitit Fresh-Start Wireframes
        :markdown 
          Built with [Fresh-Start](https://github.com/rickmesser/Fresh-Start), a beginning developer's start point with some great modern tools already baked in, Fresh-Start Wireframes strip out un-neccesary code and modules and focus on greyscale building blocks for rapid prototyping with bootstrap's responsive grid.
        %a.btn.btn-primary.btn-large{:href => "https://github.com/rickmesser/Fresh-Start"} Learn more Â»
      .row
        .span4
          %h2 Wireframes in action
          :markdown 
            Check break-points really quickly by working with pre-processors like haml and less. Everything in the project is ready to go so feel free to play around with Bootstrap's [responsive grid](http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap/scaffolding.html#gridSystem) without consequence!
          
        .span4
          %h2 Hash Out Those Ideas
          %p Test your ideas and see how sections behave on different devices.
        .span4
          %h2 Non-commital Makes It Easy
          %p Don't feel like you have to commit to things you create with this framework. Just try out an idea and if it works, great, if not, just re-start. Liberate your workflow!

